{"marker":1,"text":"= Division"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All of these were Joktan’s sons."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Shem, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 11:10–26","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 3:34–36","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":34,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Arpachshad, Shelah,"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 11:10–26","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":10},{"label":"Lk 3:34–36","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":34}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Eber, Peleg, Reu,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Serug, Nahor, Terah,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and Abram (that is, Abraham)."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Abraham’s sons: Isaac and Ishmael."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"These "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:12–16","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" are their family records: Nebaioth, Ishmael’s firstborn, Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 25:12–16","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah."},{"kind":"text","text":" These were Ishmael’s sons."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:32","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The sons "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:1–4","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" born to Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah."},{"kind":"text","text":" Jokshan’s sons: Sheba and Dedan."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 25:1–4","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:33","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Midian’s sons: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah."},{"kind":"text","text":" All of these were Keturah’s descendants."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:34","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Abraham "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 1:28","book":"1Ch","chapter":1,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" fathered Isaac."},{"kind":"text","text":" Isaac’s sons: Esau and Israel. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 25:24–26","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 32:28","book":"Gen","chapter":32,"verse":28,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Ch 1:28","book":"1Ch","chapter":1,"verse":28},{"label":"Gn 25:24–26","book":"Gen","chapter":25,"verse":24},{"label":"Gn 32:28","book":"Gen","chapter":32,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:35","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Esau’s "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:4–5","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:9","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" sons: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 36:4–5","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":4},{"label":"Gn 36:9","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:36","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Eliphaz’s sons: Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, and Kenaz; and by Timna, Amalek. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"LXX; MT reads and Timna and Amalek; Gn 36:12"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"LXX; MT reads and Timna and Amalek; Gn 36:12"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:37","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Reuel’s sons: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:38","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Seir’s "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:20–30","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" sons: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 36:20–30","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:39","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Lotan’s sons: Hori and Homam. Timna was Lotan’s sister."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:40","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Shobal’s sons: Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam."},{"kind":"text","text":" Zibeon’s sons: Aiah and Anah."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:41","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Anah’s son: Dishon."},{"kind":"text","text":" Dishon’s sons: Hamran, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:42","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Ezer’s sons: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan."},{"kind":"text","text":" Dishan’s sons: Uz and Aran."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:43","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"These "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:31–39","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" were the kings who reigned in the land of Edom"},{"kind":"text","text":" before any king reigned over the Israelites:"},{"kind":"text","text":" Bela son of Beor."},{"kind":"text","text":" Bela’s town was named Dinhabah."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 36:31–39","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":31}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:44","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Bela died, Jobab son of Zerah from Bozrah "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 34:6","book":"Isa","chapter":34,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" reigned in his place."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 34:6","book":"Isa","chapter":34,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:45","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Jobab died, Husham from the land of the Temanites "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jb 2:11","book":"Job","chapter":2,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" reigned in his place."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jb 2:11","book":"Job","chapter":2,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:46","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Husham died, Hadad son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the territory of Moab, reigned in his place."},{"kind":"text","text":" Hadad’s town was named Avith."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:47","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Hadad died, Samlah from Masrekah reigned in his place."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:48","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Samlah died, Shaul from Rehoboth on the Euphrates River reigned in his place."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:49","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Shaul died, Baal-hanan son of Achbor reigned in his place."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:50","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Baal-hanan died, Hadad reigned in his place."},{"kind":"text","text":" Hadad’s city was named Pai, and his wife’s name was Mehetabel"},{"kind":"text","text":" daughter of Matred, daughter of Me-zahab."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:51","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Hadad died."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:52","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:53","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ch:1:54","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Magdiel, and Iram."},{"kind":"text","text":" These were Edom’s chiefs."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783279426272}